If you go here, I can also recommend spending 2-3 days in Genoa, a city that is often overlooked by tourists.

node.text:
Do you notice how the houses aren’t straight? 😲
⠀
This is perfectly normal in Amsterdam, and today it’s part of the charm. They weren’t built like this though, and the leaning is caused by the soil underneath.
⠀
All of the old houses are built on wooden stilts, drilled down deep for several meters in order to reach more stable sand.
⠀
This is a similar situation to the one in Pisa and the leaning tower, where the soil under is causing it to sink.

Budapest, the Capital of Hungary 🇭🇺
⠀
The Hungarian Parliament building is one of the most beautiful in the world. The architecture is striking as are the details.
⠀
It’s especially beautiful from the other side of the Danube river, but I like this angle too as it’s another perspective that you don’t see in photos too often.
⠀
I’ve been to Budapest more times than I can count with my hands, and it’s easily one of my favorite cities in Europe.
⠀
Of course I’m a bit biased due to my Hungarian heritage, but the city has it all. The best period to visit according to me is somewhere in May/June before it gets crowded in the summer.

Havana, Cuba 🇨🇺
⠀
Traveling around Cuba is something I can definitely recommend to do!
⠀
It’s very different and unique, and sometimes challenging too, but it’s also so beautiful and interesting! 😀

Taj Mahal in India 🇮🇳
⠀
One of the most majestic buildings in the world. Up to 4 million tourists visit the Taj Mahal each year!
⠀
i was very impressed by the details and grand feeling of this place. So it’s definitely a tourist attraction that is worth the hype, in my opinion.
⠀
Capturing a photo without people is actually quite easy, as there is a photo platform in front of the palace and the water. However, it’s still tricky to get that place to yourself and the lines can get long at times.
⠀
There will still be people walking on the sides, but they are often not very noticeable unless they wear a strong color.

node.text:
Visiting New York has inspired me and I have found the passion for photography again!
⠀
Being under pressure to create content on a regularly basis can really take out the fun of the equation. I started this account 3,5 years ago to show you the beauty of the places I visit, and to inspire others to go out there and explore our amazing planet!
⠀
For the most part of 2018, I really felt less creative and I felt the need to jump the Instagram trends instead of going out there and just capture what I really wanted.
⠀

I’m really excited about 2019!
Can you spot the Empire State Building? 🙂

Do you remember that I said you could get some epic views for free while crossing Manhattan Bridge in New York? Well, this is just another view where you can see Chinatown 🙂
⠀
Watching cities from above or distance as everyday life goes by is something I always find fascinating 🙂
Do you know what DUMBO is a shortening for? 🙂

Do you enjoy street art while traveling? 🙂
⠀
New York has some really impressive murals, like this masterpiece at Chelsea Square Market with Mother Theresa and Gandhi

node.text:
Angkor Wat in Cambodia
⠀
Watching the sunrise here is on many people’s bucket lists, and from my own experience i can say that its very beautiful and something special.
⠀
Expect crowds though, If you swip to the next photo you can see a tiny part of the crowd at sunrise.
⠀
To get a good spot, you need to come here at least 1,5 hours before sunrise. It’s pitch dark outside when you arrive and you almost have to run when the gates open If you want to secure a good spot to watch the sunrise and take photos.

My thoughts today goes to the victims of yesterday’s terror attack in Tokyo. A city that is very dear to me, and a place where I never thought this would happen.
⠀
Japan is one of the safest countries i’ve ever visited. People even leave their bikes and homes unlocked.
⠀
I don’t understand what’s wrong with people who commit these crimes against humanity. Why can’t we all live in peace and harmony? Without hurting each other...
⠀
We need to realize that we are all one, and we shouldnt fight each other, but instead thrive, evolve, and take the best of every culture and society to grow and make Earth a better place.
Ask me anything about Stockholm 🙃
Tokyo Vibez 🇯🇵

Do you like Greek Food? 😍
⠀
For me, Greek Food is like heaven for my tastebuds. I love the Home-cooked meals you can find at local tavernas that are made from organic and natural food + herbs and spices.
⠀
This photo is from Santorini, and a small village called Pyrgos. We stopped here while exploring the island by scooter, and then we found this small restaurant called Penelope’s.
⠀
Swipe to see a photo of Christine and the owners ☺️ they were a lovely old couple and we stayed and chat for a bit afterwards.
⠀
Locals experiences is something that we really enjoy while traveling, and we almost never end up in a restaurant in touristy spots. Finding the hidden and authentic gems is one of best parts of traveling 🙂 as well as meeting the locals.

Did you know that Sweden has a lot of old castles? 🙂
⠀
This is Gripsholm Castle, which is possible to visit on a day trip from Stockholm! 🇸🇪

Time to share some of my favorite photos and experiences!
⠀
Torre del Mangia is one of the main attractions in Siena. You should def go here when visiting. To get this view, simply walk inside and look up 🙂

How do you celebrate Christmas in your country? I’m really looking forward to hear more and read about your traditions around the world 🙂
⠀
In Sweden, we celebrate the 24th, and eat A LOT of food, such as herring, meatballs, Skagenröra, Rödbetssallad (beetroot salad), Prince sausages, Smoked and spiced salmon (Gravlaks), red and brown cabbage, Julskinka (Christmas ham) and much more!
⠀
After or before the food (depending on family tradition) we also watch Donald Duck and other Disney series that goes on television annually (its the same thing every year).
⠀
After that, ”Santa” will come and give the presents. And then we eat a lot of candy and chocolate 😍 Swedish candy is the best in the world ❤️ i wish i could send some to all of you so that you can try!
⠀
This year, I’m in New York though and will celebrate a more Americanized version of Christmas tomorrow, the 25th.
⠀
HAPPY CHRISTMAS EVERYONE ❤️💙

How do you say Merry Christmas in your language?
⠀
In Swedish we say GOD JUL 🎄😀

Sometimes the darkness can show you the light 🌠

This year has been a real struggle for me on Instagram. The platform has changed a lot in just one year, and somewhere along the way I lost myself and the love for Instagram.
⠀
With the ever growing competition and the struggles with algorithms not showing your pictures in the feed, it’s easy to get carried away and look at what others are doing. 
I’m not sure how many or if anyone of you have noticed or feel the same, but in some ways I feel that my account went from unique to mainstream this year. I started doing the same things as others instead of doing my own thing like before.
⠀
Some places I even traveled to because of Instagram and only to get ”the shot” and it’s all so ridiculous when you think about it.

Lately I’ve also felt repulsed of what Instagram has become. Since I know how many of the most popular photos are being made, its easy for me to spot If that photo was ”in the moment” or If it was being completely staged.
⠀
This has also made me realize how silly and ”fake” Instagram has become in many ways.
⠀
In reality, i think that Instagram should be a platform with inspiration for everything. For travel that would be to inspire people to travel to new places, adventures, enjoy the places they go to as well as to interact with locals and just be present.
⠀
Our social world has a tendency to take away from the experience and stop people from living in the moment since we get so focused on taking photos and documenting it all on social medias.

I think it’s time for a change. It’s time to embrace genuine photos and to encourage authentic travel experiences that will create memories for life. 
It’s time to post photos from reality rather than staged scenes that 99% never will experience.

This is a promise to myself and all of you who follow my account. I will do my best to have fun again on the platform and post whatever I feel like and not care about any algorithms or what other people are posting.

My mission on my travel blog has always been to help others travel better and showcase the beauty of our world. I want that for my Instagram feed as well, instead of being “just another travel account”

Life is like a waterfall – always moving
⠀
What are you up to this weekend? 🙂 ===========================
Camera: Nikon D850
Settings: 1/5 sec | 22f | ISO 64

My night has become a sunny dawn because of you ❤️💙
⠀
Once again, the Hawaiian sunsets are amazing and something you shouldn’t skip while visiting the Islands 🙂

Have you visited Hawaii? 🍃
⠀ 
If you love road trips, you’ll probably enjoy the Road to Hana in Maui. Jungle and greens everywhere and plenty of stops with waterfalls, lookouts and hiking trails.
⠀
Photography tip: Always check different angles. While classic photos are great, I really enjoy finding new perspectives 🙂
⠀
Take this shot as an example, most people would photograph these two falls individually because the lookout platforms are located in front of the waterfalls.
⠀
However, just a few meters on the side of the path, you got this view over both waterfalls, and almost no one went to that spot.
⠀
So, challenge yourself and after you have taken the classic shots, see if you can bring a new perspective or make the photo more interesting by moving yourself or the camera 🙂

If you could change one thing about Instagram, what would it be?
⠀
I’ve been on this platform for almost 4 years now, and I’ve seen it change several times, for better and worse.
⠀
I’m not sure if you agree with me, but I think at least some will. In my humble opinion, If I were able to change one thing about Instagram, it would be to favor unique and creative content. In some ways, the algorithm does (sometimes) but most of the times I see the same photos all over again from the same places, just from another person.
⠀
Don’t get me wrong, I’ve done a few Instagram places myself, and also have my fair share of staged photos because it looks better in photos.
⠀
However, I have come to a point where I feel Instagram is getting less real for every day that goes on, and more and more people aim for the perfect photos and feeds, thus forgetting about what traveling is all about. I think some creativity and authenticity goes lost.
⠀
And from my own experience, some experiences are Waaaay much better without thinking about taking photos for Instagram and just enjoy the moment.
⠀
I believe its important to share that Instagram photos aren’t always reality, its only a brief moment where you don’t see behind the scenes.
⠀
I want to share even more unique places and perspectives as well as the real experiences of traveling. Instagram today is all about having the perfect photos and feeds, but is that really what we want?
⠀
Some thoughts that Im interested to hear what you think about 🙂 and no judging, because there is no right or wrong answer in this ❤️
⠀
Btw, this is me having fun running from the water at the black beach in Maui. When we visited a few days ago, the waves were high and the water was filled with Portuguese Man o War (a kind of venomous marine animal) so bathing was no good, but it was still beautiful. @christineabroad and I had the beach all to ourselves since we arrived here at sunrise 😍
📷: @christineabroad

If you’re driving the Road to Hana in Maui, you’ll drive past some really spectacular waterfalls! Most of them are accesible from the road with a parking nearby.
⠀
Photo tip: If you want to photograph waterfalls where u get the water blurred, you need to use a longer shutter speed. My camera and lens allow me to take sharp pictures hand held down to 1/5 of a second.  However most of the times you need a tripod since you wont be able to hold the camera still enough.
⠀
The longer shutter speed you have, the smoother look u will get on the water
⠀
So make sure to bring a tripod If you want to photograph waterfalls with this technique, and even better, bring a ND-filter to allow for longer shutter speeds during daylight.

node.text:
Do you go to bed early while traveling or do you stay out late? 🙂
⠀
I prefer a mix, especially when we go up early to take photos at sunrise. I need my beauty sleep 🙃 but I also like to stay out late occasionally and get a different vibe of the places we visit!

Where’s your next destination? 😀
⠀
Tomorrow, we are going to Maui, and I’m so excited to be exploring the island!

Omoide Yokocho in Tokyo 🇯🇵
⠀
Also known as memory lane, and a place where you can get an authentic Izakaya experience in Shinjuku. In these alleys you will find several bars/small restaurants serving Japanese Beer as well as yakitori, yakiniku and lots of different types of food on skewers.
⠀
It has also become a famous spot for photographers due to the iconic vibes and alleys.
Let your weird light shine bright so that the other weirdos know where to find you 🙃🌄

Are you an early bird or do you like late mornings?
⠀
This was one of my early mornings in Kyoto with @christineabroad 🙂 have you missed these photos from us?

Good morning from @ritzcarlton.osaka - One of our absolute favorite hotels 🙂 We have arrived in Hawaii now, but we finished our 19 days traveling around Japan at this lovely hotel.
⠀
If you have some Hawaii tips, let me know in the comments. We will be traveling to Maui and Kauai after Oahu 😀

Fushimi Inari Shrine 🇯🇵
⠀
I first photographed this place almost 3 years ago. Since then we have been back to Japan twice and now I visited this place again.
⠀
It’s amazing how crowded this place has become due to its popularity on Instagram and being a filmning location for the movie Memoirs of a Geisha.
⠀
3 years ago we came at sunrise and had this place all to ourselves, and it was amazing. This time, we arrived at sunrise as well, but it was already crowded.

I still recommend people to go here though, its incredible, but you will probably have to wait a while to get a photo without other people in it.

node.text:
Did you know that Tokyo is the most populated city in the world?
⠀⠀⠀⠀
Something you can definitely notice in areas such as Shibuya or Shinjuku, or during rush hour in the Metro/trains.
⠀⠀⠀⠀
However, it’s still so easy to find peaceful spots and areas with a small town feel and without lots of other people. Even in areas such as Shinjuku and Shibuya, you can Walk 2-3 blocks from the action, and find a conpletely peaceful street. 
#tokyo #japan #日本 #東京 #旅行

Can you give this deer a name? 😀🦌
⠀
Nara is an easy day trip away from Kyoto or Osaka and highly recommended 🙂 the city full of wild deer walking around + there are lots of cool temples!
⠀
If you visit, please remember to be mindful and respect these beautiful animals. Treat them as your friends, but also remember that they are wild.
Todaiji Temple in Nara 🇯🇵 also home to this giant buddha statue from the 8th century! 🙂

Tired of autumn colors yet? 🍁🍁🍁
⠀
We managed to get some of the last glimpses of Koyo season at this Unesco heritage site in Kyoto yesterday!
⠀
1 december today and 24 days to Christmas (for Swedes) and 25 for US/UK and so on, I guess most countries celebrate the 25th December.
⠀
I’m quite excited about Christmas this year as we will experience New York Christmas vibes for the first time! It looks so magical in movies, so hopefully its awesome in real life too!
⠀
What about you? 😀

Nijo Castle, Kyoto 🇯🇵
⠀⠀⠀⠀
December is approaching, and I’m thinking about sharing my favorite photos from the year. Would you like to see some mix of the best shots? 😀 let me know in the comments!

How many cats do you see in this photo? 😀 Mjaaauuu 🐈🐈🐈
⠀⠀⠀⠀
Did you know that Tokyo has a temple with hundreds (maybe even thousands) of these Neko Cats? 😀

I’m not a religious person, but Buddha’s teachings changed my life a few years ago. It taught me to be unselfish and always be kind and think positive.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I really do think that the world could benefit a lot by learning from Buddhism. Compassion and kindness is the way.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Interesting/True story: just when I was going to post this photo I saw a huge spider crawling next to me on the wall.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
A few years ago, I would probably have killed it. Some of you might feel the same way, and that’s okay because that’s unfortunately what a lot of people are being told and taught as a kid.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
However, nowadays, I just put them in a glass and get a paper on the other side and let them outside again :) or If it’s a smaller spider I just let it stay inside. Spiders are actually very important animals, and If you can, don’t kill them.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Instead have a look at the spider (many of them are actually really cute up close), and then let it outside again :) I guess the moral of the story was that a few years ago I wasn’t as compassionate that I try to be these days. Not because I wasn’t kind or didn’t care, I just didn’t think about it.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Always choose kindness and compassion 🙂 If you haven’t looked into Buddha’s teachings, I highly recommend to read more and learn about the practices.

Nature never cease to amaze me. This is Kegon Falls in Japan, one of the 3 major waterfalls in the country.

Even though we missed the best autumn colors in Nikko, it still is an incredible place filled with natural beauty and various temples with incredible details and history.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Today we arrived in Kyoto, and it looks promising with several areas in full peak color!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Have you ever been to Kyoto? 😀🇯🇵

Do you enjoy night photography?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I like to shoot cities at night, but I rarely post those photos on my Instagram account. And I tend to choose early mornings before late nights while traveling. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
If you want to learn night photography, all you really need to start is a solid tripod and a camera that allows you to adjust shutter speed.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Ever seen Sensoji temple in Tokyo without people? Nah, didn’t think so either. Maybe in the middle of the night when it’s no longer iluminated, but otherwise I think there are pretty much people all the time. This shot was taken at around 11, and If you zoom in on the photo, you will see people in it.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
However, since I have used a long shutter speed here and people are moving around, they won’t be caught in the photo as a whole, but rather as a ”ghost” dragged out and blurry. Unfortunately, most people here stop a few seconds to get a photo and then they ”stick” a little more in the frame.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
But as you can see, from a quick glance it looks empty, and since I have used a smaller aperture (f/22) the street lamp gets a nice effect that looks like a star.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Settings for this shot: 155 sec, f/22, ISO 31 with a Tamron 15-30mm and a Nikon D850.

Do you travel solo or with someone else? 🙂
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Spending 24/7 together with a person might be initimidating for some. Not for me, at least not with @christineabroad (only when she get’s hangry 😂).

Many people ask me what camera gear I use, so I wanted to share and answer that question here 🙂 I started out with a Nikon D7200 and a Tokina 11-16 mm and the kit lens 18-140mm, 3 years ago.
⠀⠀⠀⠀
1 year later I got the Nikon D500 and bought a Tamron lens 18-270mm.
⠀⠀⠀⠀
Recently I upgraded again to a full frame camera, and it has opened up new possibilities and ways of taking photos that I couldn’t do with a crop sensor camera.
⠀⠀⠀⠀
Now I use a Nikon D850 and a Tamron 15-30mm and a Nikkor 18-300mm as well as a Sigma Art 35mm.
⠀⠀⠀⠀
I wouldn’t recommend starting out with an expensive camera. In the beginning it’s more important to learn the camera and basics of photography. You can take great photos with beginner level cameras.
⠀⠀⠀⠀
But of course, there is a big difference between Nikon D850 and Nikon D7200 for example, but if the person behind the camera doesn’t know how to use it, that person won’t be able to take much advantage of the upgrade.
⠀⠀⠀⠀
The best camera is the one you always carry with you. Even smartphones are pretty great these days and give quite good quality pictures.
⠀⠀⠀⠀
Just make sure to learn your camera and the different settings. Always use manual mode with Dslrs and learn to see the light.
⠀⠀⠀⠀
When I started out photography, I watched so many YouTube videos about different techniques, composition, light and explanations of the different settings. After that, I just went out and learned by doing, and after a while I understood more and more from the YouTube videos and found my own style and technique.
⠀⠀⠀⠀
And if you’re not already shooting in RAW-format (if your camera allows it) and edit your photos in Lightroom, I highly recommend starting ASAP! 🙂
⠀⠀⠀⠀
If you have any questions, let me know!

Photography / Instagram tips - Always have a clear subject.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
If you want to get the attention of the viewer, the photo can’t be too messy. You only have 1 second before the viewer has judged your photo in their head. After that, you have either caught their attention or lost it.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
If you have a clear subject, it’s easy to look at the photo and by having a main subject in clear focus, you will get the viewer’s attention.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Take this photo for example, the Ding Ding tram is my main subject, but there are lots of other interesting stuff in the photo as well. However, the other things don’t steal the attention at first glance.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
For me, the local lady and skyscrapers are equally interesting, but you will most likely take a look at these after you’ve seen the main subject - The Ding Ding Tram.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
In Photography, and a lot of things in life, less is often more. I often see people wanting to photograph and get everything in the frame, but that can easily make the photo messy.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I will keep sharing photography and Instagram tips in every second photo I post 🙂

And Hey! 👋 I asked If you wanted me to share more photography tips or Instagram related tips as well as blogging, and a lot of you seem interested in learning more and hear what i have to share about those topics 🙂
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#1 Instagram and Photography tip: Do your research.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
This includes searching hashtags, locations, getting inspiration from others, how to get there, and sometimes to check how the sunlight will hit the place you want to visit. Light is key in photography, and If the light is too harsh and creates a lot of shadows, the photo will probably not turn out as good. (Shadows can still be cool though)
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Doing research before you go will save you time and sometimes even money, since you come prepared. It will also avoid disappointments If you go to the place when the time is right.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I always use Google Maps or ask the locals for directions 🙂 If you want to find new locations, I can also recommend the website Locationscout.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
It’s a site where photographers tag places and the website lets you search for destinations and then they show photos and places from nearby.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
You can also search in Google for sunrise and sunset times, or download an app. There are also apps and websites where you can see where the sun will be in regards to your location at a specific time.

[annons] - Just nu får du 25% rabatt på @stadium_jointhemovement i deras onlineshop när du använder koden SWEDISHNOMAD 
Koden är giltig fram tills 21 oktober 😀 och den gäller på alla varor som inte redan är rabatterade. 
Det här året har jag lovat mig själv att spendera mer tid ute i naturen. Hittills har jag och Christine hunnit med att vandra i de tyska alperna och Dolomiterna. Den senaste veckan har vi vandrat och kört runt till massor av vackra platser på Mallorca. 
Att vara ute och röra på sig är viktigt, både för vår fysiska hälsa men också för vår psykiska hälsa. Det ger ett välmående och det är extra viktigt nu när allt fler sitter still framför en dator. 
Därför är jag också glad över att få vara med och inspirera andra att resa och röra på sig genom #movewithstadium och deras initiativ att främja en aktiv livsstil! 
#stadiumjointhemovement {ENG} This year, I have promised myself to get more outdoors and leave the cities as often as possible. So far, we have been hiking in the German Alps, The Dolomites and now Mallorca. 
I have also joined an active lifestyle campaign for the Swedish brand @stadium_jointhemovement to inspire others to get outdoors 🙂

And yes, Mallorca is not all about beaches 😉 there are plenty of mountains, and some even see some snow during wintertime!

After some rainy days here in Mallorca, this morning came with sunshine! 
However, prayers goes out to the people and their families who sadly lost their lives in flash floodings. I have never thought about these things happening in Europe, yet I find myself here on the island at the same time as some of the worst rainy and stormy days in a long time. 
Me and Christine were driving up in the mountains when the heavy downpour started 2 days ago. It was quite scary going down and I feel lucky and thankful for being alive. 
Mother nature is beautiful, but also very powerful and potentially deadly as well. I wish everyone out there to think and cherish your life. Follow your dreams and never take life for granted ❤️

Thursday Motivation! - Long Caption
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Today I want to talk about dreams. In this digital era, there are so many possibilites to earn a decent living online and follow your dreams.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Want to travel The World? You don’t have to become an influencer to do it.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
For example, you can be a web designer, photographer, translator, bartender, lawyer, programmer, flight attendant, English teacher, dive instructor, YouTuber, Personal trainer, Blogger, Copywriter, SEO-staff, marketing manager, hairdresser, yoga teacher, tour guide, social media manager, customer service agent, virtual assistant and many many more!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
It all comes down to passion, being creative and seizing the moment. Take the leap of faith and learn from others who have done something similar!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I wouldn’t recommend you to just quit your job and drop everything to travel the world, because to be honest that’s not the best way to pursue things unless you have money saved.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
When you believe in yourself and realize that anything is possible, you’ll get extra energy within. Another important part is to surround yourself with positive and creative people who lifts you up rather than bringing negative thoughts into your life.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
That’s essential to get that extra energy boost you need to pursue your dreams and truly believe in yourself! ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I have been making a living online for 4 years, and it’s been such an adventure. The things I have learned along the way is not something they teach in schools, unfortunately.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
But the knowledge is out there, and once you join the Digital Nomad community and find likeminded people, you can learn so much and share with others as well. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
With this said, I want to assure you that dreams do come true, and the biggest block in your way is often yourself.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Mine and Christine’s trip to the Maldives is a  great example that dreams can come true by hard work, passion and taking a leap of faith!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Don’t limit yourself, be the best version of you every day and believe in your dreams! ❤️
If you live to be a hundred, I want to live to be a hundred minus one day so I never have to live without you 💑

Today is the Swedish National Day! 🇸🇪🇸🇪🇸🇪 And here are some fun facts about Sweden :) ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
1. 99% of Sweden’s waste gets recycled 
2. There are 95 700 Lakes 
3. You’re allowed to camp and roam freely in nature as well as pick wild berries, flowers etc.
4. We eat more than 20 million “Semlor” each year (a Swedish pastry)
5. Most popular female name is Maria
6. Most popular male name is Karl
7. We always talk about the weather
8. Gay relationship has been legalized since 1944
9. There are about 400 000 moose roaming freely in the woods
10. The Swedish word “Lagom” doesn’t have a translation
11. 1.5 million Swedes migrated to USA from 1850 to 1930
12. It’s considered very rude to walk inside someone’s home with their shoes on 
13. We drink more coffee than most other people in the world
14. The sun never rise for a couple of days during winter up in the north
15. And during summer the sun never sets for a couple of days up in the north

•
To be fully honest, before our road trip, I had never thought of traveling 4 weeks to Germany, except for the Neuschwanstein Castle and Burg Eltz. I just didn’t know enough about the country despite it being so close to Sweden. ⠀⠀⠀
•
I know many of you have been surprised over the beauty as well, after reading several of your comments! ⠀⠀⠀
•
Now, I know better. Germany has become one of my favorite countries. And i understand why many germans choose to travel within their own country instead of going abroad all the time. ⠀⠀⠀
•
•
The nature is absolutely beautiful, the villages are super cute and charming, the cities are full of life and the people are polite and friendly. ⠀⠀⠀
•
And yes, the country is home to several fairytale castles as well! ⠀⠀⠀
•
I’m so glad that we explored lots of regions and places in Germany, and I can’t wait to travel back another time to explore more :) ⠀⠀⠀

Let me know in the comment section what you think of Germany and if you would like to go there 😀 #visitgermany @germanytourism #beautifuldestinations

Why do you travel? •
•
A good question to ask yourself, just as with any other part of life. When you know why, it’s easier to make the most out of it. •
•
I started to travel because I wanted to see the world. I wanted to see all of the places from the Nat Geo documentaries I saw as a kid. •
•
That’s still a big reason why I travel, but as soon as I started to travel full-time 3 years ago, I realized that there’s more to traveling than just going to a different place. •
•
What matters as well is also the people you meet, their stories, their culture and the people you share your experiences with.
•
•
Traveling, and especially photography has taught me that the world is a lot smaller than we might expect, and a lot bigger and majestic than we also might expect. We have things in common all over the world, both with humans and animals. We all wander this earth, and traveling has taught me to appreciate our beautiful world and the magical things we find by the hands of Mother Earth.

Make sure to watch out for my stories from tomorrow and the next coming 20 days I will be showing many beautiful places, and also let you follow along on the road trip! 😀😀😀

Wroclaw, Poland 🇵🇱
•
•
Sometimes I find writing captions challenging, especially since I want my photography to speak for itself, and I want to evoke emotions and inspiration through my work.
•
•
But I guess that telling a story could also improve and be nice as well.
•
•
So, let me tell you about Poland. It’s a wonderful country that I’ve been traveling through quite extensively by train and bus. You might not know about Poland as a beautiful country, but there are so many beautiful cities to explore and lots of history.
•
•
In addition to that you also have nature and some really cool castles. The food and people are great too. Once you show some interest in the locals, or even better try to speak some #polish words and phrases, then you will really notice the hospitality in general.
•
•
And when you do visit #Poland, make sure to try some traditional vodka and pierogi! 😀 some of my favorite cities are #Wroclaw (very vegan friendly), #Krakow, #Warsaw, #Gdańsk and #Poznan!

3. And a very kind person with lots of compassion for others.
4. She doesn't love cookies as much as I do, but that's okay, more cookies for me!

What about you? Are u a solo traveler or do you travel together with your loved one, friends, or with your kids? 😀

Welcome to Poznan 🇵🇱🇵🇱🇵🇱
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I only flew here because i found a flight ticket for 4 euro per person, but I was happily surprised and Poznan actually has quite a few nice spots to see! ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
I think i will do this more often, just go somewhere i know nothing about and just explore 😊 usually we plan a lot ahead and do research on how to get around and cool places, but it's nice to travel the old-fashioned way too! ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
What about you? Do you research before visiting a place or not? 😃

Dare to live the life you've always wanted 🙌 no dreams are too big! ⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Do you have a dream? Feel free to share and inspire eachother 😊
⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
My biggest dream is to one day be able to open up a rescue center for animals. ⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
But I also dream of connecting the world through my travels, because i truly believe that we are connnected somehow, and that it's time to put our differences aside and instead see that we are all humans, and that we must take care of our planet together.

We shall appreciate our cultural differences and learn from eachother! ❤

Pick a Color 😀🙌
.
Colors are always making me happy, I dont know why but there something about colorful places! 
This is Wroclaw in Poland 😊 🇵🇱 a very beautiful city with lots of great restaurants and colorful buildings!

At least once a year, go someplace you've never been before 🌍👫 Our visit in the Maldives was one of the new countries and places we saw last year! 
This year I really hope to visit at least one country or place that most people never heard of before. 
I love to find hidden gems and unique places, and while Maldives isn't very hidden or unknown it was still truly special to spend time on your own private Island in paradise! 
Do you have a country or place you want to visit this year that you've never been to? 😀

Happy Friday! 🙌

Florence was even more beautiful than i could ever imagine before visiting last year during our 2 weeks trip in Italy! 
Have you ever been to Florence? 🇮🇹😀
#italy #florence #italiainunoscatto

#Tb to one of the most amazing places we stayed last year!

We spent the night in an @airbnb bungalow in the middle of nowhere at the Eastern side of Bali 😍 waking up here was amazing, and when you go to Bali  i really recommend @hideoutlightroom 
It has become something of an "Insta Spot", but it's truly amazing. You even have your own private outdoor bathtub! Probably the best Airbnb we've stayed at! 😃

Our plan so far is to explore places in Europe and perhaps also Africa, and now we are looking to point out more specific places and countries to visit 🙌

I really appreciate your support ❤ and I always read and try to answer the comments you post! 
Instagram as a platform has changed in many ways this year but it's still my number 1 place for inspiration, and the travel & photography community here is fantastic! 
I don't know what 2018 has in store for me, but I do know that I'm planning to make the most of it! I have never been this excited for a new year to come 😀

Did you know that a certain bamboo species can grow up to 91 cm per day? Thats almost 1 meter 🤥 and equal to 4 cm per hour 😀

With that said, we managed to find the "secret" bamboo grove in Kyoto. This is not the same as most tourists visit in Arashiyama!
.
